當你愛一個人，你必須相信他
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}SAM: [Voiceover] When you love someone, you've gotta trust them.{\r}

4
00:00:53,410 --> 00:00:54,610
別無它法
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}There's no other way.{\r}

5
00:00:55,420 --> 00:00:58,200
你得將掌管生命中一切的那把鑰匙給他
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}You've got to give them the key to everything that's yours.{\r}

6
00:00:59,340 --> 00:01:00,790
要不然有什么意義？
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Otherwise, what's the point?{\r}

7
00:01:03,590 --> 00:01:07,380
一直以來，我深信我擁有的是這樣的愛
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}And, for a while, I believed that's the kind of love I had.{\r}

8
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:17,200
在我開賭場及被炸之前…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}SAM: Before I ever ran a casino, or got blown up...{\r}

9
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:19,870
艾斯羅斯坦，可是最屌的賽馬預測者
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Ace Rothstein was a hell of a handicapper.{\r}

10
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,160
我告訴你
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I can tell you that.{\r}

11
00:03:21,380 --> 00:03:24,330
我旺到每次只要我下注，全國的賭盤賠率…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I was so good that whenever I bet, I'd change the odds...{\r}

12
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:26,120
都會隨著改變
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}for every bookmaker in the country.{\r}

13
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:28,590
不蓋你，我對賽馬的研究精湛到…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I'm serious, I had it down so cold...{\r}

14
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:31,080
讓我晉升人間天堂
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}that I was given paradise on Earth.{\r}

15
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:35,680
我被升為拉斯維加斯最大賭場之一《坦吉樂》的管理人…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I was given one of the biggest casinos in Las Vegas to run, the Tangiers...{\r}

16
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:40,050
唯有聘請我的那幫人才能如此大手筆
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}by the only kind of guys that can actually get you that kind of money.{\r}

17
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:43,060
六千兩百七十萬美元
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}$62, 700, 000.{\r}

18
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:45,020
我不知道細節
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I don't know all the details.{\r}

19
00:03:45,150 --> 00:03:47,730
老實說，沒人知道細節…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}NICKY: [Voiceover] In fact, nobody knew all the details...{\r}

20
00:03:47,870 --> 00:03:49,410
原本應該很完美的
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}but it should've been perfect.{\r}

21
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:53,780
他有我這好友尼奇山多羅挺他…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}He had me, Nicky Santoro, his best friend, watching his ass...{\r}

22
00:03:54,290 --> 00:03:57,660
他手中也攬著他愛的女人，金吉兒
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}and he had Ginger, the woman he loved, on his arm.{\r}

23
00:03:58,340 --> 00:04:00,870
到頭來，我們全搞砸了
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}But in the end, we fucked it all up.{\r}

24
00:04:01,130 --> 00:04:03,090
原本應多完美
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}It should've been so sweet, too.{\r}

25
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:06,750
結果，我們這樣的小混混…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}It turned out to be the last time that street guys like us...{\r}

26
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:09,550
在這次之后就再也無緣搞油水這么豐富的大生意了
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}were ever given anything that fucking valuable again.{\r}

27
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,720
那時的賭城，是蠢蛋們…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}SAM: Vegas was a place where suckers...{\r}

28
00:04:16,860 --> 00:04:18,730
一毛一毛存足了錢飛來…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}flew in every year on their own nickel...{\r}

29
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:20,900
直到輸光了家當才走人的地方
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}and left behind about a billion dollars.{\r}

30
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:25,240
在夜晚，你看不到包圍拉斯維加斯的沙漠
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}But at night, you couldn't see the desert that surrounds Las Vegas.{\r}

31
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:31,110
但城里許多的問題卻都是在沙漠里解決的
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}But it's in the desert where lots of the town's problems are solved.{\r}

32
00:04:31,460 --> 00:04:33,250
沙漠里的坑洞可多著呢
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}NICKY: Got a lot of holes in the desert...{\r}

33
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:35,750
里面埋藏了很多問題
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}and a lot of problems are buried in those holes.{\r}

34
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,160
只是程序要對
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Except you gotta do it right.{\r}

35
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,920
你得先把洞挖好…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}You gotta have the hole already dug...{\r}

36
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:42,260
再將貨從汽車后車箱載來
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}before you show up with a package in the trunk.{\r}

37
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:46,210
要不然你就得在沙漠挖上個30到45分鐘
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Otherwise, you're talking about 30 or 45 minutes of digging.{\r}

38
00:04:46,350 --> 00:04:48,970
誰又知道期間會有什么人出現？
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Who knows who's gonna be coming along in that time?{\r}

39
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:51,940
不知不覺中，你又得多挖好幾個洞
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Before you know it, you gotta dig a few more holes.{\r}

40
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,900
搞不好一整晚都得耗在那兒
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}You could be there all fucking night.{\r}

41
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:56,810
公爵

42
00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:04,480
坦吉樂

43
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:08,670
精華地段-拉斯維加斯，十年前
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}THE STRIP - LAS VEGAS TEN YEARS EARLIER{\r}

44
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:12,490
誰抗拒的了？
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}SAM: Who could resist?{\r}

45
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:15,340
在別處，我只是個登記賽馬的一個賭徒…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Anywhere else, I was a bookie, a gambler...{\r}

46
00:05:15,470 --> 00:05:18,750
老是得小心翼翼，成天被條子們騷擾
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}always looking over my shoulder, hassled by cops, day and night.{\r}

47
00:05:18,890 --> 00:05:20,800
但在這兒，我可是羅斯坦先生
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}But here, I'm Mr. Rothstein.{\r}

48
00:05:20,930 --> 00:05:23,600
不但不偷雞摸狗，還管間賭場
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I'm not only legitimate, but running a casino.{\r}

49
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:26,440
那就像是將夢想換為現金
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}And that's like selling people dreams for cash.{\r}

50
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:31,600
我聘任了賭場的一個老朋友 比利雪伯當經理，然后開始工作
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I hired an old casino pal, Billy Sherbert, as my manager, and went to work.{\r}

51
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:35,320
這是負責牌室的羅尼
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}And this is Ronnie, who takes care of the card room.{\r}

52
00:05:37,990 --> 00:05:40,950
像我們這種人 拉斯維加斯洗去了我們的罪孽
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}SAM: For guys like me, Las Vegas washes away your sins.{\r}

53
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,070
像是道德洗車場一樣
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}It's like a morality car wash.{\r}

54
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:46,660
它對我們的效用就像法國露德 對駝背和殘障的人一樣
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}It does for us what Lourdes does for humpbacks and cripples.{\r}

55
00:05:53,590 --> 00:05:55,720
不但讓我們重見天日…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}SAM: And along with making us legit...{\r}

56
00:05:56,220 --> 00:05:58,800
還帶來了現金，數不盡的錢
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}comes cash, tons of it.{\r}

57
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:01,770
不然你以為我們沒事 跑到這沙漠中央干嘛？
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}What do you think we're doing here in the middle of the desert?{\r}

58
00:06:01,850 --> 00:06:03,400
就是為了這些錢
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}It's all this money.{\r}

59
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:07,320
這是所有炫目的燈光…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}This is the end result of all the bright lights...{\r}

60
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:10,480
所有的招待、香檳、免費住宿…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}and the comped trips, of all the champagne...{\r}

61
00:06:10,610 --> 00:06:14,660
女人與喝不完的酒 最終所造成的結果
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}and free hotel suites, and all the broads and all the booze.{\r}

62
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:18,910
全都是為了 讓我們弄走你的錢
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}It's all been arranged just for us to get your money.{\r}

63
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,290
這就是賭城的真面目
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}That's the truth about Las Vegas.{\r}

64
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:25,800
我們是唯一的贏家
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}We're the only winners.{\r}

65
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:27,960
賭徒們一點機會都沒有
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}The players don't stand a chance.{\r}

66
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:30,630
而他們的錢從賭桌上…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}And their cash flows from the tables...{\r}

67
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,340
流入我們的收銀柜再進入保險籠…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}to our boxes through the cage...{\r}

68
00:06:33,470 --> 00:06:36,340
最后流入全賭場最神圣的房間
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}and into the most sacred room in the casino.{\r}

69
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,470
他們計算錢的地方…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}The place where they add up all the money...{\r}

70
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:42,140
注意-請勿進入 萬物之首，計算室
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}the Holy of holies, the count room.{\r}

71
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:46,730
這兒可不是閑雜人等可進出的
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Now, this place was off-limits.{\r}

72
00:06:47,410 --> 00:06:48,780
連我都進不去
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Even I couldn't get inside.{\r}

73
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:51,780
當然，但我的工作是讓它保持 滿滿的狀態
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}But it was my job to keep it filled with cash. That's for sure.{\r}

74
00:06:51,910 --> 00:06:53,950
里頭的錢多到…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}NICKY: They had so much money in there...{\r}

75
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,650
可讓你用百元大鈔砌棟房子
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}you could build a house out of stacks of $100 bills.{\r}

76
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,460
最棒的是…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}And the best part was that upstairs...{\r}

77
00:06:58,590 --> 00:07:01,540
上頭董事會什么屁都不知道
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}the Board of Directors didn't know what the fuck was going on.{\r}

78
00:07:01,710 --> 00:07:03,920
在他們看來一切都干凈俐落 沒人動手腳
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}To them everything looked on the up-and-up.{\r}

79
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,540
不是嗎？當然不
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Right? Wrong.{\r}

80
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,880
確認五千元
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Verify $5,000.{\r}

81
00:07:06,970 --> 00:07:08,680
在計算室的那些人…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}NICKY: The guys in the counting room...{\r}

82
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:12,350
都是被派進去將里頭吸干的
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}were all slipped in there to skim the joint dry.{\r}

83
00:07:12,850 --> 00:07:15,430
他們會少算錢，將計單弄掉
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}They'd do short counts, they'd lose fill slips.{\r}

84
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,020
甚至直接從箱里拿走現款
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}They'd even take cash right out of the drop-boxes.{\r}

85
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:19,980
全是靠這家伙…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}And it was up to this guy right here...{\r}

86
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:22,270
站在兩百萬元前的這位…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}standing in front of $2 million...{\r}

87
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:25,610
在被國稅局或任何人發現前…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}to skim the cash off the top without anybody getting wise...{\r}

88
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:27,490
把錢摸走
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}the IRS or anybody.{\r}

89
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:31,160
在計算室里 好像都沒人在看
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Notice how in the count room nobody ever seems to see anything.{\r}

90
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,530
不知怎的，大家都視若無睹
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Somehow, somebody's always looking the other way.{\r}

91
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:35,830
看看這些家伙 他們看來真忙，不是嗎？
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Look at these guys. They look busy, right?{\r}

92
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,380
他們在算錢，誰會吵他們呢？
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}They're counting money. Who wants to bother them?{\r}

93
00:07:38,550 --> 00:07:41,800
我的意思是，天曉得他們會不會 犯了錯而忘記偷錢
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}I mean, God forbid they should make a mistake and forget to steal.{\r}

94
00:07:42,140 --> 00:07:44,670
這期間，你可來去自如
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Meanwhile, you're in and you're out.{\r}

95
00:07:45,810 --> 00:07:48,590
走過那些鳥事不干的警衛 每禮拜還多拿一百元…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Past the jag-off guard who gets an extra $100 a week...{\r}

96
00:07:48,730 --> 00:07:50,100
只為了看門
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}just to watch the door.{\r}

97
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:53,020
一如往常一樣規律…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}It's routine. Business as usual...{\r}

98
00:07:53,150 --> 00:07:55,850
走進、走出、你好、再見
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}in, out, hello, goodbye.{\r}

99
00:07:55,990 --> 00:07:57,360
就這么簡單
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}That's all there is to it.{\r}

100
00:07:57,450 --> 00:08:01,030
就只是個拎著皮箱 走出賭場的肥豬
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Just another fat fuck walking out of a casino with a suitcase.{\r}

101
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,780
但那口箱子 會直接送往一個地方
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Now, that suitcase was going straight to one place:{\r}

102
00:08:04,910 --> 00:08:07,620
堪薩斯市，那里是…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}right to Kansas City, which was as close...{\r}

103
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,990
中部的老大能離拉斯維加斯 最近的地方…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}to Las Vegas as the Midwest bosses could go...{\r}

104
00:08:10,130 --> 00:08:12,000
而不用怕被逮捕
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}without getting themselves arrested.{\r}

105
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:16,250
堪薩斯市 老大們要的只是那口箱子
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}That suitcase was all the bosses ever wanted.{\r}

106
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:18,880
每個月都要
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}And they wanted it every month.{\r}

107
00:08:19,890 --> 00:08:21,760
圣馬利諾意大利超市

108
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,390
這個摩門教的混蛋…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Now this old Mormon fuck here...{\r}

109
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:29,860
他每個月都得拿著箱子飛來
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}he had to fly in with suitcases once a month, nice and easy.{\r}

110
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:32,770
-什么東西這么香？ -他們做了好料的
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}-Something smells good. -They made us something to eat.{\r}

111
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,780
老大們會從各地飛來…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}NICKY: The bosses would come from all over:{\r}

112
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,400
底特律、克里夫蘭、密爾瓦基…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Detroit, Cleveland, Milwaukee...{\r}

113
00:08:37,530 --> 00:08:38,910
整個中西部…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}all over the Midwest...{\r}

114
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:42,410
他們都會在這個位于 堪薩斯市的市場碰面
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}and they would meet in this produce market in Kansas City.{\r}

115
00:08:42,540 --> 00:08:44,000
根本沒人會知道
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Nobody even knew it.{\r}

116
00:08:44,710 --> 00:08:46,830
有一個讓他媽做菜
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}One of the guys made his mother do the cooking.{\r}

117
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,000
你有看到杰瑞史塔瑞歐嗎？
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}Do you ever see that guy Jerry Steriano?{\r}

118
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:51,750
這些老頭們看來可能不怎么樣
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}NICKY: These old greaseballs might not look it...{\r}

119
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,080
但相信我…
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}but believe me...{\r}

120
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:56,140
他們才是賭城的秘密操縱者
{\fn微軟雅黑}{\fs14}these are the guys who secretly controlled Las Vegas.{\r}

